snippet.textDisplay:
aha! the great Sudarshan faakir gets featured in cokestudio. Do hear the version of this that made this ghazal famous, it was sung by Jagjit singh and Chitra singh. This one sounds a bit slow but very well executed. The original one I referred to by Jagjit singh was fast paced, more like a Geet. This one sounds sweet and mellow and that's not a bad thing. Zaw's range is super and must be celebrated...Somehow the English part spoiled the song for me but then that is just me. I am quite touchy about Jagjit singh and Ghazals because for me both mean one and the same. Sajjad Ali's voice can never age. Never.

Excellent effort!
Love from India
@Rohwit
